        <header class="entry-header">
            <h1 class="entry-title">Dr. Siting Liu Won 1st Place at the ACM Student Research Competition at ICCAD 2024</h1>
            <div class="entry-meta">
                
                 <div class="clear"></div>
            </div>
        </header><!-- .entry-header -->

        <div class="entry-content">
            <p>We are thrilled to announce that Dr. Siting Liu has won <strong>1st place</strong> in the prestigious <strong>ACM Student Research Competition (SRC)</strong> held at ICCAD 2024. This remarkable achievement is a testament to Dr. Liu’s outstanding research contributions and academic excellence in the field of VLSI placement and routing optimization.</p>
<p>Dr. Liu’s winning research, titled &#8220;<strong>Enhancing Efficiency and Quality for Routing Stage</strong>&#8221; addresses critical challenges in the VLSI design flow, demonstrating innovative solutions with practical applications.</p>
<p>Dr. Liu has an impressive track record of academic achievements. She has authored several papers published in top-tier conferences, including ISPD’24, IJCAI’23, DAC’23, DATE’22, DATE’21, and ASPDAC’21. Notably, she received the <strong>Best Paper Award</strong> for her work on GPU acceleration for VLSI global routing algorithms (DATE’22) and a <strong>Best Paper Award Nomination</strong> for her research on high-level synthesis optimization (DATE’21).</p>
<p>As the 1st place winner of the ACM SIGDA Student Research Competition, Dr. Liu will now advance to the <strong>ACM-wide Student Research Competition Grand Finals</strong>, where she will compete with top student researchers from other ACM Special Interest Groups. SIGDA, a prominent ACM Special Interest Group, is dedicated to advancing the knowledge and skills of electronic design automation professionals and students worldwide.</p>
<p>Congratulations to Dr. Siting Liu on this incredible achievement! We wish her the best of luck in the ACM-wide Grand Finals and look forward to her continued success in advancing the field of VLSI design automation.</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/achievement/original/siting-src-award-1-scaled.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full" src="/wp-content/uploads/achievement/original/siting-src-award-1-scaled.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="600" /></a><br />
